WHAT IT DOES?
=============
MTK feature, it's used to set the configuration about CrossMount.
Devices can be connected by CrossMount. If device A mounted device B's some service , such 
as camera , A can use B's camera.


HOW IT WAS BUILT?
==================
It's dependent on the  jar library of com.mediatek.crossmount.adapter/discovery
and it's an application in Launcher.


HOW TO USE IT?
==============
1) entrance: Launcher--> CrossMount

2) share service to other devices: CrossMount --> 
Menu "Service sharing"

3) mount some services from other device: 
 click the available devices list in the main entrance
 
4) trust list: like "White name list". 
 
          

All the source code of this module were written by MediaTek co..
